⚙️ METHODOLOGY
1. Object-Oriented Approach
A class Book is used to represent each book
Encapsulation is used (private data + public methods)
2. File Handling (Binary Files)
Data stored in library.dat
Uses:
ofstream → write data
ifstream → read data
fstream → update data
Records stored using:
write() and read() functions
3. Persistent Storage
Data is saved permanently in files
Even after program closes, records remain
4. Sequential Access
Records are accessed one by one
Searching is done using linear search
5. Update Technique
For modifying records:
File pointer repositioned using seekp()
Overwrites existing record
6. Deletion Strategy
Uses temporary file method
Safer approach:
Copy valid records → temp file
Replace original file
7. User Interaction
Menu-driven program
Uses loop (do-while) for continuous execution
8. Data Members Handling
bookID → Unique identifier
title, author → Stored as character arrays
issued → Boolean status tracking


